    {
      "kind": {
        "Brief": {
          "id": "theory",
          "title": "Theory:",
          "brief_html": "<p>Computing $a^k \\pmod m$ by raising $a$ to the $k$ first fails for large exponents. Intermediate values explode before the final <code>% m</code>.</p>\n<p>Square-and-multiply processes bits of $k$: square the base each step, multiply into the result when the current bit is 1. Julia's <code>powermod(a, k, m)</code> uses this internally.</p>\n"
        }
      },
      "execution": {
